1
00:00:05,360 --> 00:00:06,820
OK 准备好了
Okay,we're set.

2
00:00:07,790 --> 00:00:11,450
本周晚些时候 国会将对筹建新一代航空母舰
Later this week,Congress will be voting on a $14 billion appropriation

3
00:00:11,560 --> 00:00:14,760
所需的140亿拨款进行投票表决
for construction of a new class aircraft carrier.

4
00:00:14,900 --> 00:00:17,920
一些监管机构认为应该将这笔款项
Many watchdog groups feel that the money would be better spent at home,

5
00:00:17,990 --> 00:00:19,640
用到住房 学校和公共设施上去
on schools and infrastructure.

6
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:20,850
您怎么认为呢?
Your opinion?

7
00:00:20,940 --> 00:00:24,630
那个...呃 这个问题很难回答
Well... uh,that's a difficult question for me to answer.

8
00:00:24,750 --> 00:00:27,620
我不知道军方需要什么
I don't really know what the military needs.

9
00:00:27,780 --> 00:00:30,170
这是先生们应该关心的问题
That's a husband question.

10
00:00:30,290 --> 00:00:33,020
我需要和我家先生探讨下 才能知道我的真是感受
I'd have to talk to him to see how I feel about it.

11
00:00:33,470 --> 00:00:36,790
谢谢 您的诚实真是让人耳目一新
Thank you. Your honesty is refreshing.

12
00:00:37,140 --> 00:00:38,630
OK 可以了
Okay,we're good.

13
00:00:38,790 --> 00:00:40,440
Chad 那个拿着相机的人
Chad,the guy with the camera over there.

14
00:00:40,520 --> 00:00:42,110
打扰下 先生 我们是ZNN电视台的
Excuse me,sir,ZNN.

15
00:00:42,190 --> 00:00:44,010
能采访下您吗? 用于晚间报道
Can we interview you for the evening news?

16
00:00:44,090 --> 00:00:45,590
- 不行 不行 - 只耽误您几分钟
- No. No. - It'll only take a second.

17
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:46,940
走开 别拿摄像机对着我
Please,don't point that at me.

18
00:00:47,030 --> 00:00:49,420
麻烦您了 先生 如果可以...
Please,sir,if you could just...

19
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:57,830
快打911!
Someone call 911!

20
00:01:27,850 --> 00:01:31,680
<font color="#B1D20E">海军罪案调查处 第九季 第04集</font>
 >

21
00:01:33,660 --> 00:01:35,080
Gibbs Gibbs Gibbs Gibbs Gibbs
Gibbs,Gibbs,Gibbs,Gibbs,Gibbs.

22
00:01:35,160 --> 00:01:36,950
什么 什么 Abby 什么 什么?
Whoa,whoa,Abby,what,what?

23
00:01:37,060 --> 00:01:39,680
你会吃惊的 我被选中了 我的匹配上了
You're not going to believe it.I was chosen.I'm a match.

24
00:01:39,790 --> 00:01:42,060
他们要我马上去医院面谈
They want me down at the hospital for an interview right away.

25
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:43,990
什么 你又去捐骨髓了?
What,you donating bone marrow again?

26
00:01:44,060 --> 00:01:45,350
不 是捐肾
No. A kidney.

27
00:01:45,380 --> 00:01:46,550
谁需要肾移植?
Who do you know that needs a kidney?

28
00:01:46,580 --> 00:01:47,410
我不认识他
I don't know him.

29
00:01:47,460 --> 00:01:48,370
我是自愿的
I just volunteered.

30
00:01:48,450 --> 00:01:51,130
Abby 慢慢说 从头说起 你到底在说什么?
Abby,slow down.Back up.What are you talking about?

31
00:01:51,220 --> 00:01:52,170
我在教堂里听说的
I heard about it at church.

32
00:01:52,210 --> 00:01:55,130
有个18岁的孩子 在做透析 他需要个肾
There's this 18-year-old kid,he's on dialysis,and he needs a kidney,

33
00:01:55,250 --> 00:01:57,940
他家里没人匹配的上 那我不能不见义勇为咯
but nobody in his family was a match,so I had to do something.

34
00:01:58,050 --> 00:02:00,100
所以我去医院做了测试 他们刚刚打电话给我
So I went down to the hospital and got tested,and they just called me.

35
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:02,470
你要把一颗健全的肾 捐给一个陌生人?
You're going to give a perfectly good kidney to a total stranger?

36
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:03,670
你疯了吗?
Are you out of your mind?

37
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:04,840
这么做很伟大
That is very noble.

38
00:02:04,930 --> 00:02:06,450
Abby 这是个大手术
Abby,that's major surgery.

39
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:08,560
需要多长时间修养? 要好几个星期啊
What's the recovery time on that?It's gotta be weeks.

40
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:10,760
不知道 我会想办法的
Well,I don't know,but I'll find out.

41
00:02:10,860 --> 00:02:13,690
我1小时后要去和 器官捐赠联络员面谈
I have an interview with the transplant coordinator in,like,an hour.

42
00:02:13,820 --> 00:02:15,550
嘿 Gibbs
Hey,Gibbs.

43
00:02:16,370 --> 00:02:18,490
嘿 Sportelli警探 你在这里做什么? 好久不见了啊
Hey,Detective Sportelli,what are you doing here?Long time.

44
00:02:18,590 --> 00:02:19,560
我得走了
I gotta go.

45
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:21,470
Abby 表给我什么事都答应
Abby,don't you commit to anything.

46
00:02:21,590 --> 00:02:23,810
会很棒的
It's gonna be great.

47
00:02:25,030 --> 00:02:26,090
Sportelli 什么事?
Sportelli,what's up?

48
00:02:26,230 --> 00:02:28,200
我抓到冷冻杀手了
I arrested The Cooler.

49
00:02:29,890 --> 00:02:33,070
怎么了 FBI头号通缉犯啊
Come on,FBI's most-wanted list.

50
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:34,450
这可是头等大功啊
It's a career-making bust.

51
00:02:34,510 --> 00:02:36,370
- 冷冻杀手? - 他把死者藏到冰柜里啊
- The Cooler? - He puts people on ice.

52
00:02:36,470 --> 00:02:40,720
他犯下半打以上备受瞩目 的买凶杀人案
Yeah,he's suspected in at least a half-dozen high-profile contract assassinations.

53
00:02:40,820 --> 00:02:44,210
- 是滴 - 死者身上取下的子弹是这些案子的连通点
- Right. - The only thing tying the cases together is the slugs taken from the victims.

54
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:46,700
是的 他像个幽灵 人间蒸发了
Yeah,he's been like a ghost,blending into the background.

55
00:02:46,790 --> 00:02:49,410
FBI压根不知道他长啥样 更别说名字了
FBI has no idea what he looks like,let alone have a name.

56
00:02:49,470 --> 00:02:50,650
他们现在有眉目了
They got one now.

57
00:02:50,750 --> 00:02:53,460
Paul Arliss 他在郊区活得很舒坦呢
Paul Arliss.He's been living e good life in suburbia.

58
00:02:53,530 --> 00:02:55,980
住在伍德利公园的一个死巷子里
On a cul-de-sac in Woodley Park.

59
00:02:56,070 --> 00:02:57,000
你们怎么抓到他的?
How'd you catch him?

60
00:02:57,070 --> 00:02:58,540
电视台在街上采访
News crew doing on-the-street interviews.

61
00:02:58,600 --> 00:03:01,360
他想躲开摄影机 结果被车撞了
He tried to avoid the camera and ran into traffic.

62
00:03:01,490 --> 00:03:02,910
被辆厢式货车撞飞的
Got hit by a van.

63
00:03:02,990 --> 00:03:04,320
目前危在旦夕
He's in critical condition.

64
00:03:04,390 --> 00:03:06,410
昨晚在新闻里看到撞飞的画面了
I saw footage of that on the news last night.

65
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:09,240
新闻里可没说他是逃犯什么的
They did not mention anything about him being a fugitive.

66
00:03:09,350 --> 00:03:11,470
在查出他身份之前我们做了保密工作
We kept it quiet till we figured out who he was.

67
00:03:11,550 --> 00:03:13,880
那是要多保密才行啊
You gotta keep that quiet.

68
00:03:14,970 --> 00:03:16,540
可不能让任何人知道啊
You wouldn't want anyone to know.

69
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:18,210
干得好 Sportelli警探
Great work,Detective Sportelli.

70
00:03:18,270 --> 00:03:19,830
你逮捕了个不省人事的大男人
You arrested the unconscious man.

71
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:22,510
他躺在人行道上后 你有把他拷起来吗?
Did you have to cuff him when he was down on the sidewalk there?

72
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:27,240
怎么查出他身份的?
How'd you I.D. him?

73
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:31,250
他携带的武器被查出涉及4宗未破案件
Ballistics tied the weapon he was carrying to four unsolved hits.

74
00:03:31,370 --> 00:03:32,500
你来这里幸灾乐祸?
You here to gloat?

75
00:03:32,590 --> 00:03:34,320
不 我是来帮你们的
No,I'm here to help you.

76
00:03:34,460 --> 00:03:39,830
我们在一街区外找到他的车 里面有监视照片和手写笔记
We found surveillance photos and handwritten notes in his car,parked about a block away.

77
00:03:40,130 --> 00:03:44,640
貌似他的下一个目标是 海军少校指挥官Geoffrey Brett
Looks like his next target is going to be a Navy Lieutenant Commander named Geoffrey Brett.

78
00:03:45,930 --> 00:03:48,990
- 知道是谁雇了Arliss? - 不知道
- You got any leads on who hired Arliss? - Nope.

79
00:03:49,080 --> 00:03:50,870
我们要审问他 他在哪里?
Well,we need to interview him.Where is he?

80
00:03:50,940 --> 00:03:53,480
华盛顿综合医院监狱病房
Washington General Hospital prison ward.

81
00:03:53,620 --> 00:03:55,910
他能讲话了 我就通知你
I'll call you when he's able to speak.

82
00:03:55,990 --> 00:03:57,960
非常出色的警探工作 Sportelli
Great detective work,Sportelli.

83
00:03:58,040 --> 00:04:00,070
我们都为你感到骄傲
I think we're all very proud of you.

84
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:02,380
乐意效劳 DiNozzo
Always a pleasure,DiNozzo.

85
00:04:04,190 --> 00:04:06,840
Brett指挥官科班出身
Boss,Commander Brett's an Academy grad.

86
00:04:06,920 --> 00:04:10,450
顶级飞行员 伊拉克战争和阿富汗战争中 驾驶F-18大黄蜂战斗机
Top Gun pilot.Flew F-18 Hornets in Iraq and Afghanistan.

87
00:04:10,550 --> 00:04:12,990
在库纳尔省被击落 (阿富汗西部中间)
Got shot down over Kunar Province.

88
00:04:13,110 --> 00:04:14,300
等等
Wait a second.

89
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:19,490
我知道他 在躲避塔利班的追杀时 他靠吃泥土 树皮和虫子为生
I know him.That's the guy that survived by eating mud,bark and bugs while evading the Taliban.

90
00:04:19,590 --> 00:04:22,910
是的 海军陆战队花了2周时间找到并救出他
Yep.Took the Marines two weeks to find and rescue him.

91
00:04:23,740 --> 00:04:25,360
猛人一个啊
One tough S.O.B.

92
00:04:25,430 --> 00:04:27,030
离异 育有一女
He's divorced,has one daughter.

93
00:04:27,150 --> 00:04:31,320
目前被委任到军事委员会 从事立法活动
Currently assigned as a legislative fellow to the House Armed Services Committee.

94
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:38,850
下午好 Brett海军少校办公室
Good afternoon.Lieutenant Commander Brett's office.

95
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:42,410
你说这个人想杀死我
You say this guy was trying to kill me.

96
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:44,400
证据充分
Got a good reason to believe so.

97
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:46,690
他是被通缉的职业杀手
He's a wanted contract killer.

98
00:04:47,570 --> 00:04:49,240
太疯狂了
This is crazy.

99
00:04:49,310 --> 00:04:51,000
我想不出有谁想杀死我
I can't think of anyone who would want me dead.

100
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:53,980
那... 呃 这玩笑开大了吧
So,uh,it's got to be a joke.

101
00:04:55,690 --> 00:04:57,580
Thornton上校派你们来的 对吧?
Captain Thornton put you up to this,didn't he?

102
00:04:57,710 --> 00:04:59,090
我不认识Thornton上校
I don't know Captain Thornton.

103
00:04:59,190 --> 00:05:01,910
那肯定是哪里出错了
Well,clearly this must be some sort of mistake.

104
00:05:02,810 --> 00:05:04,990
当地警方拿着可靠证据来找我们的
Metro police came to us with solid evidence.

105
00:05:05,140 --> 00:05:08,010
你说这家伙已经被捕了 那我没什么好担心的咯
Well,you said the guy's been caught,so there's nothing to worry about.

106
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:10,310
雇凶杀你的人 是想你死
Whoever hired him to kill you,wants you dead.

107
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:12,710
他们可以再雇另外的人
They'll find someone else to do the job.

108
00:05:12,790 --> 00:05:16,140
我们希望对你进行保护 直到我们查到更多线索
We would like to put you in protective custody until we know more.

109
00:05:16,210 --> 00:05:17,820
开玩笑吧?
You're serious?

110
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:20,850
我能照顾好自己
I can take care of myself.

111
00:05:22,540 --> 00:05:25,730
我的工作是给军事委员会成员提意见
My job is to advise the members of the Armed Services Committee.

112
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:30,460
即将有个大额军费开支的投票要进行
There's a critical vote about to take place on the Hill regarding a substantial military expenditure.

113
00:05:30,570 --> 00:05:32,450
我这周要参加一系列的敏感性会议
I'm going to be in sensitive meetings all week.

114
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:34,590
要不你工作时 派个探员保护你
Why don't you let an agent shadow you at work.

115
00:05:34,660 --> 00:05:37,420
今晚你就在海军基地的军官宿舍里住下
We'll set you up tonight at the officers' quarters at the Navy Yard.

116
00:05:37,490 --> 00:05:40,010
我不知道 我...
Yeah,I don't know,I've...

117
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:44,920
哪个探员来保护我?
And who will be the agent shadowing me?

118
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:56,820
- 嗨 Ducky - 稍等片刻 Abby
- Hi,Ducky. - Just a second,Abby.

119
00:05:56,890 --> 00:06:02,750
我刚清理完 并给加了润滑油 霍恩比推出了跟我同名的模型
I'm just finishing cleaning and lubricating the Hornby model of my namesake-- "The Mallard.

120
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:04,420
无比华丽的野鸭牌火车头
" Magnificent locomotive.

121
00:06:04,570 --> 00:06:09,150
它在1938年创造了世界速度纪录
It set the world speed record for a steam engine back in 1938.

122
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:11,660
每小时126英里(203千米)
126 miles per hour.

123
00:06:11,770 --> 00:06:15,900
它在Bytham村和Essendine村之间有点走下坡路
It was on a slight downgrade between Bytham and Essendine.

124
00:06:16,790 --> 00:06:22,920
一直使用到1960年...Abby?
Remained in service until 1960... Abby?

125
00:06:23,830 --> 00:06:25,550
怎么了?
What's the matter?

126
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:26,860
有空么?
Do you have a minute?

127
00:06:26,940 --> 00:06:27,940
嗯
Certainly.

128
00:06:28,060 --> 00:06:29,300
我刚从医院回来
I just came from the hospital.

129
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:36,530
听说了 捐肾可不是个轻易的决定
I heard.Donating a kidney is not a decision to be taken lightly.

130
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:40,670
器官捐赠联络员说我不是唯一的匹配
The transplant coordinator said that I'm not the only one that's a match.

131
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:41,920
还有个家伙
There's also a guy.

132
00:06:41,980 --> 00:06:42,990
真的?
Really?

133
00:06:43,090 --> 00:06:45,860
一般能找到一个匹配者就很难
Well,usually it's hard to find one donor that's a match.

134
00:06:45,950 --> 00:06:46,910
是的 没错
Yeah,exactly.

135
00:06:46,950 --> 00:06:51,100
所以她很吃惊有两兄妹同时愿意
That's why she was amazed that she found a brother and a sister both willing to donate.

136
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:53,740
你弟也是自愿的?
Your brother also volunteered?

137
00:06:53,790 --> 00:06:55,830
不是 我跟Luca谈过了
No. I spoke to Luca.

138
00:06:55,870 --> 00:06:57,280
他什么都不知道
He doesn't know anything about it.

139
00:06:57,390 --> 00:06:59,080
我有点糊涂了
I'm confused.

140
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:04,950
为什么器官捐赠联络员认为 你和那男的是兄妹?
Why does the transplant coordinator think that you and this man are siblings?

141
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:09,300
在筛选过程中 我们要提供线粒体DNA样本
As part of the screening process,we had to give a mitochondrial DNA sample.

142
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:11,850
我们俩的完全匹配 Ducky
Ours was a dead-on match,Ducky.

143
00:07:12,510 --> 00:07:15,420
匹配率大于99.9%
More than 99.9%.

144
00:07:15,530 --> 00:07:19,420
我们是绝对的亲兄妹 对吧?
I mean,we have to be full-on brother and sister,right?

145
00:07:19,490 --> 00:07:23,390
我联系联络员想要他的详细资料 --像名字和地址之类
I-I pressed the coordinator for details on the guy-- like his name and address,

146
00:07:23,470 --> 00:07:25,820
但她拒绝了 说她已经说了太多
but she clammed up,saying she'd said too much already.

147
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:30,730
所有捐赠者的医疗和个人信息都 必须按规定保密
It's pro forma for all donors' medical and personal records to be kept confidential.

148
00:07:30,820 --> 00:07:36,440
难道是我父母还有个小孩被人领养?
Could my parents have had another child they gave up for adoption?

149
00:07:36,620 --> 00:07:39,170
这事讲不通啊
I mean,it doesn't make any sense.

150
00:07:39,270 --> 00:07:41,630
我不信 我弟弟Luca也不信
I don't believe it.And neither does my little brother Luca.

151
00:07:41,780 --> 00:07:43,600
他跟我一样吃惊
He's as blown away as I am.

152
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:48,820
你父母都去世了 还有其他人可以打听么?
With your parents deceased,isn't there anyone else you can ask?

153
00:07:50,950 --> 00:07:52,690
谢谢你
Thanks for listening.

154
00:07:57,610 --> 00:07:59,260
我们应该等Gibbs一起
I think we should have waited for Gibbs.

155
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:00,130
没时间了
No time.

156
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:01,730
Sportelli说他清醒了
Sportelli said he was conscious.

157
00:08:01,850 --> 00:08:05,390
不知道醒了多久了 听着 等下我们进去 你别说话
We don't know for how long.Now,listen,when we get into the room,you let me do the talking.

158
00:08:05,730 --> 00:08:06,970
为什么?
Why?

159
00:08:07,050 --> 00:08:08,970
The Cooler逃避FBI的追捕很多年了
The Cooler's evaded the FBI for years.

160
00:08:09,070 --> 00:08:12,610
得有妙招才能让他说出谁想杀Brett中校
Getting him to tell us who took out the hit on Commander Brett is going to take a deft hand.

161
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:14,120
你能行?
Oh,and that's you?

162
00:08:14,180 --> 00:08:16,730
我告诉你前 你甚至不知道冷冻杀手是什么
You didn't even know who The Cooler was until I told you.

163
00:08:17,060 --> 00:08:18,780
Ziva也不知道
Neither did Ziva.

164
00:08:18,830 --> 00:08:21,990
不 我需要跟Arliss单独谈谈 所以你得把Sportelli拦在外头
No,I need to talk to Arliss alone,so you've got to get Sportelli out of the room.

165
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,410
我要怎么做啊?
And how am I supposed to do that?

166
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:25,110
不知道--反正分散他的注意力
Well,I don't know-- you distract him.

167
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:29,080
讲讲你对喷气发动机组件的痴迷-- 就是把人困在火箭里的那玩意
Talk about your stupid obsession with jet packs-- men strapped to rockets.

168
00:08:29,180 --> 00:08:30,970
我那才不是痴迷
Hey,I am not obsessed.

169
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:32,640
特别探员们
Special agents.

170
00:08:32,770 --> 00:08:34,730
伙计们 你们不能跟Arliss谈话
You're not going to get to talk to Arliss,boys.

171
00:08:34,820 --> 00:08:36,860
- 你说我们可以 - 他心跳停了
- You said we could. - He flatlined.

172
00:08:36,930 --> 00:08:40,410
- 死了? - 没错
- He's dead? - Over and out.

173
00:08:47,780 --> 00:08:50,000
难以置信这家伙是个声名狼藉的杀手
Hard to believe this guy was an infamous killer.

174
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:53,180
到昨天为止 他唯一的荣誉就是 作为厂商代表获得
Up until yesterday,his only claim to fame was salesman of the year

175
00:08:53,290 --> 00:08:56,200
一家家具公司的年度杰出业务员
as a manufacturer's rep for a furniture company.

176
00:08:56,310 --> 00:08:59,790
他有老婆和两个孩子 无犯罪记录 连张停车罚单也没有
He's got a wife,two kids,no criminal record.Not even a parking ticket.

177
00:08:59,900 --> 00:09:02,760
他隐匿的很好 逃避FBI好多年了
He evaded the FBI for years by hiding in plain sight.

178
00:09:02,870 --> 00:09:07,030
- 挺怪的 你还不得不佩服这家伙... - 他杀人如麻
- In a weird way,you got to admire the guy... - He's a mass murderer.

179
00:09:07,140 --> 00:09:09,040
卑鄙之极
Despicable.

180
00:09:09,140 --> 00:09:10,130
没什么好佩服的
Nothing to admire.

181
00:09:10,210 --> 00:09:11,840
你有没有找到Arliss跟 认识Brett中校的人之间的联系?
Did you connect Arliss to anyone who knows Commander Brett?

182
00:09:11,910 --> 00:09:14,000
还没 当地警察已经派人去查他家
not yet .Metro's got a team going through his house.

183
00:09:14,150 --> 00:09:16,200
我要是能审问他 不是我吹
If only I could have interrogated him,I tell ya.

184
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:21,010
不出5分钟 我就能让他乖乖吐出 那凶手的名字
Five minutes in my magic hands and I would have had him coughing up the name of that hit man.

185
00:09:21,060 --> 00:09:25,040
- 5分钟? - 没错 因为我是跟最强的人学习
- Five minutes? - Five minutes,because I learned from the best.

186
00:09:25,190 --> 00:09:26,550
我们得找出背后黑手
We need to find out who hired him.

187
00:09:26,610 --> 00:09:27,770
我在找他的仇人
I've been looking for enemies.

188
00:09:27,820 --> 00:09:31,730
不过Brett中校是个战功赫赫的英雄 大家都喜欢他
But Commander Brett is a decorated hero.He's well-liked.

189
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:36,370
他的前指挥官说Brett挤进国会时 曾踩过某些人
Spoke to his former C.O. Brett climbed over some people while angling for his plum assignment on the Hill,

190
00:09:36,420 --> 00:09:38,300
不过这位置他确实应得
but no one denies he deserved it.

191
00:09:38,340 --> 00:09:41,220
当他挤进国会时? 谁讲话会这样?
While angling for his plum assignment on the Hill?Who talks like that?

192
00:09:44,260 --> 00:09:46,160
我已经迟到5分钟了
I'm already five minutes late.

193
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:47,790
你平时都这么忙?
Is your day always this busy?

194
00:09:47,860 --> 00:09:49,210
有时候更忙
Some are worse.

195
00:09:49,250 --> 00:09:50,840
特别是有投票的时候
Especially when there's a big vote.

196
00:09:52,610 --> 00:09:55,720
这是第一次一位武装女性陪同我
It's the first time I've ever been accompanied by a woman who's packing.

197
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:59,320
- 武装? - 带着枪
- Packing? - Carrying a gun.

198
00:09:59,860 --> 00:10:03,180
像你这样的人怎么会做NCIS的探员?
Why does someone who looks like you become an NCIS agent?

199
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:04,800
那探员应该长什么样?
What are agents supposed to look like?

200
00:10:04,870 --> 00:10:07,480
严肃 傲慢 无趣
Stern,surly,humorless.

201
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:08,510
比如探员Gibbs
Agent Gibbs.

202
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:11,940
你们的问题是绷得太紧了
The problem with you guys is you're too uptight.

203
00:10:12,460 --> 00:10:14,110
放轻松点
Try lightening up a little.

204
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:18,760
探员Ziva 没事 我认识他 没事
Agent Ziva,relax.I know him.Relax.

205
00:10:20,060 --> 00:10:20,950
抱歉 Nick
Sorry,Nick.

206
00:10:21,030 --> 00:10:23,010
- 你还好吗? - 是 不!
- You okay? - Yeah.No!

207
00:10:23,140 --> 00:10:24,110
这到底怎么回事?
What the hell is going on?

208
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:26,330
Nick 这是NCIS特别探员Ziva David
Nick,NCIS Special Agent Ziva David.

209
00:10:27,470 --> 00:10:30,600
- NCIS? - 他们误以为我需要保护
- NCIS? - They mistakenly believe I need protection.

210
00:10:30,690 --> 00:10:31,590
其实真没什么事
It's nothing really.

211
00:10:31,670 --> 00:10:33,560
你刚刚粗暴对待了一名K大街的大亨
You just roughed up one of the barons of K Street.

212
00:10:33,630 --> 00:10:35,780
他是说得好听点 其实我就是个说客
He's trying to avoid using the pejorative.I'm a lobbyist.

213
00:10:35,950 --> 00:10:38,550
你今天下午稍后会在办公室吗? 我有事要跟你谈
Listen,are you going to be in your office later this afternoon?I need to talk to you about something.

214
00:10:38,660 --> 00:10:39,980
好的 我4点左右回来
Yeah,I'll be back around 4:00.

215
00:10:40,050 --> 00:10:42,840
好极了 很高兴认识你
Okay,great.Nice meeting you,I think.

216
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:51,780
谢谢你的"小心翼翼"
Thanks for being so discreet.

217
00:10:57,450 --> 00:10:59,750
DiNozzo这是在搞什么?
What the hell's DiNozzo doing?

218
00:11:03,150 --> 00:11:05,080
不知道
I don't know.

219
00:11:08,230 --> 00:11:09,740
你确定Arliss的老婆没问题么?
Are you sure about Arliss' wife?

220
00:11:09,820 --> 00:11:11,850
她以为当时他在路上卖家具呢
She thought he was on the road,selling furniture.

221
00:11:11,910 --> 00:11:14,220
随便你 跟她谈也好 四处看看也行
Be my guest.Talk to her. Look around.

222
00:11:14,370 --> 00:11:16,260
不过最好快点
Better move fast.

223
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:17,960
FBI马上就来
FBI's on their way.

224
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:19,390
他们会接管一切
They're taking over.

225
00:11:19,490 --> 00:11:20,860
我讨厌这些家伙
Hate those guys.

226
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,080
都是些钓名沽誉的
Glory hounds.

227
00:11:22,150 --> 00:11:23,830
比起局里 我还是喜欢跟你打交道
I'd rather deal with you than the Bureau.

228
00:11:23,890 --> 00:11:24,900
我刚可不是说你
I don't blame you.

229
00:11:24,970 --> 00:11:26,910
老大!
Hey,boss!

230
00:11:31,410 --> 00:11:35,050
这儿有问题 我步测过车库的内外
Something's wrong here.I paced off the inside and outside of the garage.

231
00:11:35,190 --> 00:11:36,710
相差几英尺
There's a couple feet missing.

232
00:11:36,780 --> 00:11:39,430
这堵墙后有电源
Looks like there's some electrical power going behind this wall.

233
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:46,290
听起来是空的
Sounds hollow.

234
00:11:46,470 --> 00:11:48,210
里面有东西
There's something back here.

235
00:11:54,110 --> 00:11:55,680
这儿有条缝
There's a seam.

236
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,650
有意思
That's interesting.

237
00:12:14,930 --> 00:12:16,550
找到了
Eureka.

238
00:12:16,650 --> 00:12:18,290
FBI有得忙了
The FBI'S gonna have a field day.

239
00:12:18,340 --> 00:12:20,260
没错
Oh,yeah,they will.

240
00:12:22,330 --> 00:12:23,960
我们能拿走电脑么?
Do you want to let us take the computer?

241
00:12:24,050 --> 00:12:25,290
我们的人很厉害
Our people are real good.

242
00:12:25,380 --> 00:12:27,950
没错 我们的人很厉害
<i>Yeah,our people are real good.</i>

243
00:12:28,030 --> 00:12:29,620
那你得告诉我你的发现 Gibbs
You'll tell me what you find,Gibbs.

244
00:12:29,690 --> 00:12:31,740
当然 没问题
Yeah,sure.

245
00:12:33,740 --> 00:12:38,460
不 跟赌金没有任何关系
No,this doesn't have anything to do with a sweepstakes.

246
00:12:38,770 --> 00:12:40,000
我...
I...

247
00:12:41,810 --> 00:12:46,780
不 我是Abigail 你侄女... 记得Gloria的女儿吗?
No,no,I'm Abigail,your niece... Gloria's daughter?

248
00:12:46,850 --> 00:12:47,700
你在干嘛?
What're you doing?

249
00:12:47,780 --> 00:12:49,240
我在Arliss的电脑里发现了线索
I found something on Arliss' computer.

250
00:12:49,280 --> 00:12:52,110
我要复制他的硬盘 你有3口的USB集线器吗?
I need to clone his hard drive.Do you have your USB-3 cable?

251
00:12:52,180 --> 00:12:53,630
有的
Oh,yeah.

252
00:12:54,660 --> 00:12:58,320
不 不 我不再是啦啦队队长了
No,no,I'm not a cheerleader anymore.

253
00:12:58,940 --> 00:13:01,490
我从高中毕业很多年了
I graduated high school a long time ago.

254
00:13:01,610 --> 00:13:03,630
呃 对不起
Um,I'm sorry.

255
00:13:03,740 --> 00:13:05,590
我现在没法给你带糖果了
I can't bring you bonbons now.

256
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:08,430
现在住在华盛顿特区
I live in Washington,DC now.

257
00:13:08,820 --> 00:13:11,660
我会来看你的 我保证
I'll visit soon,yeah,I promise.

258
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:13,970
不 我是Abby
No,this is,this is Abby.

259
00:13:14,910 --> 00:13:16,750
Abby Sciuto
Abby Sciuto.

260
00:13:16,850 --> 00:13:22,110
好吧 Gert婶婶 去吃饭吧
Okay,Aunt Gert,go have your dinner.

261
00:13:23,140 --> 00:13:26,300
好的 爱你噢 再见
Okay. Love you. Bye.

262
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:34,900
Abby 你没事吧?
Abby,you okay?

263
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:38,320
我想会不会有人知道 我父母抛弃过一个小孩
I just thought if anyone would know about my parents giving up a child,

264
00:13:38,370 --> 00:13:42,530
那是我婶婶Gert 但她甚至不记得自己的名字 真杯具
it'd be my Aunt Gert,but she can't even remember her own name,poor thing.

265
00:13:42,630 --> 00:13:44,990
她的老年痴呆很严重
Her dementia's gotten so bad.

266
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:46,740
这是你婶婶?
That your aunt?

267
00:13:46,850 --> 00:13:49,160
不 这是我妈妈
No,it's my mom.

268
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:51,150
哇 她好漂亮
Wow,she was beautiful.

269
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:53,600
她是很美
She was beautiful.

270
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:54,910
你发现什么了?
What'd you find?

271
00:13:54,970 --> 00:13:57,070
Arliss被卡车撞到的前一天
Well,the day before Arliss was hit by the truck,

272
00:13:57,190 --> 00:14:02,540
收到了一笔25,000刀的转帐汇款 钱来自于一个叫George Kaplan的经纪人帐户
he received a $25,000 wire transfer from the brokerage account of a "George Kaplan.

273
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:04,470
25,000刀
" $25,000.

274
00:14:04,710 --> 00:14:07,710
现在这些钱够买凶的?
That's how much it costs to get somebody whacked these days?

275
00:14:07,790 --> 00:14:13,510
Kaplan先生住在Branchport大道1313号 西北边 房号3C
Mr.Kaplan lives at 1313 Branchport Avenue,Northwest,apartment 3C.

276
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:17,160
Abby?
Abby?

277
00:14:20,020 --> 00:14:24,840
我很想晚上见你 亲爱的 但是爸爸有事情 必须呆在城里 好吗?
I wish you could spend the night,honey,but something has come up and Daddy has to stay in the city,okay?

278
00:14:24,920 --> 00:14:26,170
我会和你妈妈谈的
I'll talk to your mother.

279
00:14:26,350 --> 00:14:29,200
看看周末怎么安排
We'll see if we can work out something for the weekend.

280
00:14:29,390 --> 00:14:30,740
会的 我保证
Yes,I promise.

281
00:14:30,850 --> 00:14:33,700
爱你 宝贝 再见
Okay,I love you,sweetheart. Bye.

282
00:14:34,330 --> 00:14:36,800
- 她多大了? - 8岁
- How old is she? - Eight.

283
00:14:37,910 --> 00:14:42,190
她需要特别的照顾 但又不愿意拖累她妈妈
She,uh,she has special needs,but she doesn't let it stop her.

284
00:14:43,070 --> 00:14:45,270
她是个好孩子
She's a great kid.

285
00:14:46,870 --> 00:14:48,500
真可爱
She's adorable.

286
00:14:48,550 --> 00:14:52,060
- 她叫什么名字? - Matilda 我叫她Tilly
- What's her name? - Matilda.I call her Tilly.

287
00:14:52,930 --> 00:14:54,750
她就是我的全部
She's my life.

288
00:14:55,140 --> 00:14:56,670
Gibbs探员 有线索吗
Agent Gibbs.You found something.

289
00:14:56,730 --> 00:14:58,710
你认识一个叫George Kaplan的人吗?
You know a man named George Kaplan?

290
00:14:59,420 --> 00:15:01,430
不认识 怎么?
No.Should I?

291
00:15:01,520 --> 00:15:03,420
我们认为他的目标就是你
We believe he put out the hit on you.

292
00:15:04,020 --> 00:15:06,130
他曾被捕过吗?
Well,has he been arrested?

293
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:09,180
不 还没 刚查到他地址
No,not yet.We got a lead on an address.

294
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:10,560
我们还在找他
We're still looking for him.

295
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:11,920
越来越不可思议
This is getting crazier.

296
00:15:12,010 --> 00:15:14,800
为什么素不相识的人要取我性命?
Why would someone I don't know want to have me killed?

297
00:15:15,830 --> 00:15:18,340
我要不要担心我女儿呢?
It's... Should I be concerned about my daughter?

298
00:15:19,340 --> 00:15:22,260
我前妻把Tilly带到Hilton Head她父母家了
My ex wanted to take Tilly to her parent's house in Hilton Head.

299
00:15:22,380 --> 00:15:24,220
我要提醒她多加小心
I'm gonna tell her to do it.

300
00:15:31,490 --> 00:15:33,410
你希望看到什么?
What do you expect to see?

301
00:15:33,540 --> 00:15:37,940
不知道 一个甩两万五出来买凶的人 不应该住这种地方
I don't know.You'd think a guy who popped 25 grand for a hit would live in better digs than this.

302
00:15:38,050 --> 00:15:39,800
我应该找人来修理一下的
I've been meaning on getting that fixed.

303
00:15:41,910 --> 00:15:44,350
老大 这位是房东 Roach小姐
Boss,this is the landlady,Mrs. Roach.

304
00:15:44,450 --> 00:15:47,740
老大 我理解你没有带搜查证
Understand you don't have a warrant,boss.

305
00:15:47,870 --> 00:15:49,120
如果你要我就弄一个给你
I can get one if you want.

306
00:15:49,210 --> 00:15:50,490
给你们省点事
Let's get this over with.

307
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:52,640
我跟Judy法官很熟
I'm missing Judge Judy.

308
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:07,850
Kaplan品味真差
Kaplan's got terrible taste.

309
00:16:07,930 --> 00:16:09,480
公寓是带家具出租的
The apartment comes furnished.

310
00:16:09,580 --> 00:16:10,940
这些都是我挑的
I picked everything out.

311
00:16:10,980 --> 00:16:12,410
Kaplan在这儿住了多久?
How long's Kaplan been living here?

312
00:16:12,470 --> 00:16:14,350
一年多吧 可能是一年半
Over a year.Maybe a year and a half.

313
00:16:14,430 --> 00:16:15,190
衣柜里没有衣服
No clothes in the closet.

314
00:16:15,290 --> 00:16:16,540
没有食物
No food.

315
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:18,400
你最后一次见到Kaplan是什么时候?
When's the last time you saw Kaplan?

316
00:16:18,490 --> 00:16:19,780
就是他来租公寓的那天
When I rented him the apartment.

317
00:16:19,890 --> 00:16:21,880
- 然后你再也没见过他? - 我看是的
- You haven't seen him since? - Don't think so.

318
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:24,820
有人租了你的房子但是不住 你不觉得奇怪吗?
You don't find it strange that someone rents an apartment from you then doesn't use it?

319
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:26,560
他是我的最佳租户
He's my best tenant.

320
00:16:26,650 --> 00:16:27,710
一点也不吵
Doesn't make any noise.

321
00:16:27,780 --> 00:16:31,000
他的业务经理每个月都按时寄支票给我
His business manager sends a check,every month,on time.

322
00:16:31,090 --> 00:16:33,980
住这种地方的人还有业务经理?
Guy who lives in this dump like this has a business manager?

323
00:16:35,180 --> 00:16:36,260
无意冒犯
No offense.

324
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:37,810
那业务经理叫什么名字?
What's the business manager's name?

325
00:16:37,910 --> 00:16:41,160
不知道 我是说 他的名字在我房里
I don't know.I mean,I got the name in my apartment.

326
00:16:43,160 --> 00:16:45,600
你是不是想让我下去拿呀
Now I suppose you want me to go down and get it.

327
00:16:50,520 --> 00:16:52,680
老大 你要不要和我一起来呢?
You wanna come with me,boss?

328
00:16:58,350 --> 00:16:59,880
我就在这里等
I'll wait here.

329
00:17:02,090 --> 00:17:04,650
20年能把一土耳其秃鹰 变成饥渴老熟女
That's what they call a "turkey vulture."20 years past a cougar.

330
00:17:04,750 --> 00:17:07,300
还是喜欢到处捕猎 不过太老有心无力了
Still likes to hunt,but too old to take down the prey.

331
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:10,190
才不是呢
I wouldn't bet on that.

332
00:17:12,170 --> 00:17:15,240
- 要不要扫指纹 老大? - 要啊
- Dust for prints,boss? - Yeah.

333
